JOHANNESBURG - Secretary of Parliament, Gengezi Mgidlana is facing disciplinary action. The action follows an internal parliamentary probe into allegations of corruption and maladministration. READ: Parliamentary workers celebrate Mgidlana suspension The National Health Education & Allied Workers Union (Nehawu) accused Mgidlana of among other things, awarding himself an education bursary and going on overseas trips. Mgidlana has seven days to explain why he should not be suspended until the finalisation of the process. He’s denied the charges and has been on special leave since June. eNCA